      <div type="description" n="monument">
        <head>Description of Monument</head>
        <p>A rectangular <rs type="material" key="marmor">white marble</rs> <rs type="objectType"><rs type="objectType">statue base</rs> shaft</rs> (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">1.01</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.48</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.60</measure>) with moulding, broken above and below. The stone was re-used; on the opposite face there is a half-moon in relief, suggesting that it perhaps had had a religious function. It stood rather awkwardly on a plinth formed by cutting down another base.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="text">
        <head>Description of Text</head>
        <p><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> on upper moulding (line 1) and on face below (lines 2 ff.)</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="letters">
        <head>Description of Letters</head>
        <p>Av. <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.04</measure>, clear but irregular; abbreviations: scroll in ll.5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 10: letter above line in ll. 3, 6, 10; l. 6, <foreign lang="grc">Κ<g type="scroll"/></foreign>, line above second <foreign lang="grc">Ο</foreign> in <foreign lang="grc">ΕΠΑΙΧΟ</foreign>.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="date">
        <head>Date</head>
        <p><date notAfter="0533" exact="none" notBefore="0468">Late fifth/early sixth century</date> (<rs type="criteria">titulature</rs>).</p>
      </div>

